
      ggHiggs


Inclusive Higgs cross-section in gluon fusion up to next-to-next-to-next-to leading order

This code computes the cross-section for the inclusive Higgs production in gluon fusion at NLO, NNLO and N3LO.
The cross-sections can also be computed using an approximation based on a combination of optimized soft-collinear and high-energy behaviours.
At NLO and NNLO the exact result is also provided (in the large-mt limit and with full top mass dependence, see Credits).
The recent N3LO result in the large-mt limit is also implemented.

The results are based on the paper:

R.D. Ball, M. Bonvini, S. Forte, S. Marzani and G. Ridolfi, arXiv:1303.3590 [hep-ph]
M. Bonvini, R.D. Ball, S. Forte, S. Marzani and G. Ridolfi, arXiv:1404.3204 [hep-ph]
M. Bonvini, S. Marzani, C. Muselli and L. Rottoli, arXiv:1603.08000 [hep-ph] (version 3.x onwards)
T. Ahmed, M. Bonvini, M.C. Kumar, P. Mathews, N. Rana, V. Ravindran and L. Rottoli, arXiv:1606.00837 [hep-ph] (for pseudo-scalar Higgs production, version 3.3+)

Please cite them if you use this code.

All updates are availabel at https://www.ge.infn.it/~bonvini/higgs/



Installation
----------------

Install gfortran, LHAPDF (5 or 6), GSL and CUBA.

Specify the path to the CUBA installation in the first (effective)
line of the Makefile:

CUBA_PATH = /write/here/your/path/to/CUBA

and if needed also the one to gfortran

Then type:

> make

This should create the library libggHiggs.a (takes a while)
and then create the two executables ggHiggs and ggHiggs-verbose.


Usage
----------------

To run try

> ./ggHiggs -h
> ./ggHiggs-verbose -h



Please report any problem to marco.bonvini@ge.infn.it


